&gt; My two main methods of running tests are
&gt; 1) the full suite via ant/junitreport, which scans for java file
&gt; patterns to collect the tests
&gt; 2) one-off or single TestCase suite invocations from a shell, using a
&gt; main method for the TestCase class
&gt;
&gt; I use a helper class in almost all the main methods, so using a
&gt; decorator could work for #2, but it doesn&#39;t help #1 without modifying
&gt; the ant target underlying code or finding a new one.
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; On Sep 8, 2004, at 1:02 PM, Neil Swingler wrote:
&gt;
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; You could introduce a decorator for the TestCase which could null it&#39;s
&gt;&gt; reference to the real TestCase as soon as it has finished executing.
